questions.text: Can you please pinpoint the exact location of your back pain and where you feel the tingling sensation in your stomach area?
When did your back pain and stomach tingling first begin, and have these symptoms been continuous or do they come and go?

Could you describe the character of your back pain (e.g., sharp, dull, shooting)? And for the stomach, can you clarify what 'tingling pain' feels like (e.g., burning, pins and needles, a crawling sensation)?
Does your back pain radiate or travel to other areas, such as down your legs? Do you experience any numbness, tingling, or weakness in your legs or feet?
What activities, positions, or foods make your back pain or stomach discomfort better or worse?
Have you noticed any other symptoms alongside these, such as fever, unexplained weight loss, changes in your bowel habits, or issues with urination?
